scripts to setup strong swan, create the tun device and route packets via the the tun device

Overview Steps: (Detail steps are presented in each sub folder)
* compile and install strongswan
* copy all the credential files (ipsec.secrets and the certificates for server and ca) in the respective folders (/data/etc)
* compile code to generate the tunnel
* create the tunnel and setup routing tables
* sudo tun-route.o & to make sure it is run as a background process
* copy the _updown and pkt capture scripts to the lib/ipsec directories as given in the README in that folder
* compile bro and install it
* copy the config files for bro to ensure packets from the tun device are being analyzed by bro
* run broctl install 
* broctl start &
* /data/usr/sbin/ipsec start
